<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ The two Interior
Ministry buildings hit by NATO cruise missiles overnight smoldered
on Saturday in Belgrade's morning haze, collapsed in on themselves
at wacky angles. They provided angry citizens evidence both of
NATO's astounding accuracy _ Yugoslav authorities said there were
no casualties of any kind _ and of the alliance's vow to strike
military and security headquarters, even in the heart of Serbia's
capital. By Steven Erlanger.
