<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES (Kukes, Albania) _ If NATO's air raid strategy
was meant to prevent Serbian forces from committing atrocities
against ethnic Albanians in Kosovo, as President Clinton and other
officials have said, it is an utter failure. The stark evidence of
that failure is in the haunted eyes of more than a quarter-million
refugees who have already been driven out of Kosovo in Slobodan
Milosevic's systematic, brutally efficient Serbian campaign to
depopulate the province of its majority Albanian population. A news
analysis. By John Kifner.
