<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SEASON-ONETIMERS (Undated) _ The major-league season starts
Sunday and, as is always the case, dozens of rookies will see
stardom looming before them. But for all their promise, at least a
few of them will become answers to a trivia question, appearing but
once. Then something _ injuries or fate or their own abilities _
will keep them from ever coming back. Countless ballplayers have
come up to the major leagues for the proverbial cup of coffee, but
only a few hundred have tasted the demitasse of a single game _
often at the end of blowouts or in the waning days of a losing
season. Most were standouts at every previous level of play. Some
bask in those memories. For others, their short careers still gnaw
at or embarrass them. By David Margolick.
</P>
