   TRASH _WASHINGTON _ A titanic struggle is developing over a
humble issue: Who will control the country's garbage? When Allied
Waste Industries of Scottsdale, Ariz., completes the takeover of
Browning-Ferris Industries of Houston, the two largest trash
haulers in the country will control half of its solid waste. The
consolidation appears to have major economic and environmental
implications. (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
