<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MLB-OPENER _ The baseball season opens in Mexico for the
first time, as the Padres play the Mets on Sunday night. (Stinson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   REDS-PREVIEW _ There is new optimism with the Reds fans because
so much has changed. There is the cosmetic _ new-look caps and
added facial hair. But some changes are more substantive. A
50-homer outfielder in Greg Vaughn. And two proven starting
pitchers _ Steve Avery and Denny Neagle. Add those players to a
team that already has Pete Harnisch and Barry Larkin alongside a
young nucleus _ Sean Casey and Dmitri Young _ and you can see why
the Reds fans believe this team can compete in the weak National
League Central. (McCoy, Dayton Daily News). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-LEMKE _ Mark Lemke can't remember the collision in Boston
last May that turned his life upside down. The next eight months of
headaches and misery are something he wishes he could forget. Now
the former Atlanta Braves second baseman says he is feeling fine
again, but he is out of the game he loves. Lemke works out each day
and waits for agent Lonnie Cooper's phone to ring. ``I'm not ready
to retire,'' says Lemke, 33. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA JOURNAL-CONSTITUTION BASEBALL SECTION
</P>
<P>
   BBN-JORDAN _ Like most professional baseball players, Braves
outfielder Brian Jordan, obtained from St. Louis during the
offseason, had to make a decision on what sport to play. Jordan's
decision came later than most. Jordan played pro baseball and
football before opting for a baseball career. We profile his career
and let him explain what went into his decision. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 45. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BBN-DONBAYLOR _ Chances are the Atlanta Braves would have made
no moves with the coaching staff until former Colorado manager Don
Baylor became available. Braves GM John Schuerholz saw the
opportunity to bring Baylor to Atlanta as a hitting coach and
jumped at the chance. Baylor saw the opportunity to join a
high-caliber team in a high-caliber TV market and figured the
exposure wouldn't hurt his resume. Baylor is expected to work with
Atlanta's young hitters _ Klesko and A.Jones _ in an effort to
eliminate easy outs from the lineup. But he's also sitting a few
feet from Braves manager Bobby Cox, who has drawn some criticism
for Atlanta's poor playoff performances. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BBN-LATINOS-BRAVES _ After ``mining'' Javy Lopez from Latin
America, the Braves made a conscious effort to set up shop there
with a minor league facility. The result, in part, has been a
strong Latin contingency on the 1999 team that includes Lopez,
Andres Galarraga, Eddie Perez, Bruce Chen, Andruw Jones and Ozzie
Guillen. (Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. MOVED
