<P>
   BBO-BASEBALL-STATUS _ When we last left baseball, Mark McGwire
and Sammy Sosa were hitting huge home runs, and the New York
Yankees were winning a World Series. Baseball, everyone said, was
back. But was it? Attendance in 1998 increased by 500 a game _ and
that's with the addition of a new franchise. Fox and the Murdoch
group, as feared, was beginning to push a baseball payroll to $96
million, almost $30 million more than any other club. Certainly the
McGwire story meant a lot to the game, but the sport seems dead set
on shooting itself in the foot. That could come sooner than later.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 50. MOVED
