<P>
   BKO-HOSKINS _ DAYTON, Ohio - Before she became a local
celebrity, basketball had always been an escape for Brandi Hoskins.
Something fun, something to do, something to take her mind off her
mother's illness and pain. An eighth grader at MacFarlane Middle
School, she had the audacity to think of the sport as a game. But
now it's getting confusing. Nobody leaves her alone. She hasn't yet
said where she'll attend high school and college coaches already
are writing her letters, planting seeds. This is the story of how
one girl's decision has become everybody's business. (Lance, Dayton
Daily News). 45. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
