<P>
   KOSOVO-MAIN _ WASHINGTON _ NATO readies more attacks against
Yugoslavia as Western leaders scramble to provide emergency
supplies and troops to help hundreds of thousands of Kosovo
Albanian refugees. Developing. (Shepard, Cox News Service) 25.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-COSTS _ WASHINGTON _ What is the Kosovo military action
costing the United States? (Malone, Cox News Service) 30.
</P>
<P>
   w/KOSOVO-COSTS-DATA.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES _ ALBANIA _ The hundreds of thousands of
refugees streaming across the border from Kosovo have escaped from
one hell into another. Thankful to be alive, they now live in
muddy, garbage-strewn fields, totally dependent on international
relief efforts to supply them with food and shelter. (Roughton, Cox
News Service) 25.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PURGE _ MONTENEGRO, Yugoslavia _ Refugees from Kosovo are
arriving with stories of executions and unspeakable acts of
brutality by Serb soldiers. (Holmes/Deans, Cox News Service) 25.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   GOALS-2000 _ WASHINGTON _ The nation isn't going to meet a
single one of the eight educational goals set for next year in the
``Goals 2000'' program, according to the 18-member state-federal
panel set up to monitor progress toward the goals. Some states will
fulfill some goals, but none will reach all eight. Why it happened,
and what will happen next. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   w/GOALS-LIST _ The eight goals, and each Cox state's progress in
achieving them. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   GOALS-DATA _ Thumbnail drawings illustrating the list of 8
national education goals have been placed in the National folder on
the Cox server. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   All stories MOVED Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   TRASH _WASHINGTON _ A titanic struggle is developing over a
humble issue: Who will control the country's garbage? When Allied
Waste Industries of Scottsdale, Ariz., completes the takeover of
Browning-Ferris Industries of Houston, the two largest trash
haulers in the country will control half of its solid waste. The
consolidation appears to have major economic and environmental
implications. (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   w/TRASH-DATA _ Largest landfills in the Cox states;
consolidation in the trash-hauling industry. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   MOVED Tuesday.
</P>
