</P>
<P>
   LOTTO-ROLLOVER _ ATLANTA _The jackpot in the multistate Big Game
lottery drawing grew to $190 million. None of the tickets sold for
Friday's $160 million drawing matched all five lotto numbers and
the Big Money Ball. The next drawing will be Tuesday. The winning
numbers from Friday's drawing were: 8, 25, 26, 28, 35. The Big
Money Ball number was 25. (Anderson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-DEATH _ Detailed story on a small enclave in East Texas
and the mixed emotions residents are feeling after one member of
community charged with slaying two neighbors and friends. 75
(Longview News Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ACOG-FUNDS _ ATLANTA _ The last time the Atlanta Committee
for the Olympic Games reported publicly on its finances, it said
there was nothing left for the city and it owed a big debt to the
national Olympic committee. However, nearly $11 million remains in
the bank account. During the past two years, tens of millions of
dollars have changed hands between ACOG, its contractors, its
executive staff, its lawyers and the tiny Georgia Amateur Athletics
Foundation. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 50.
</P>
